<p>Maher Alarfaj, Ph.D. (<a href="https://www.ohio.edu/">Ohio University</a>), is a Saudi full professor. His interests lie at the intersection of education, science (particularly neuroscience) and quantitative research. He is interested in contributing to the conceptual frameworks that seek to build bridges between science and social science. He was a Hubert H. Humphrey fellow. He has won grants from international associations, such as the UNESCO. He has 23 years of experience with Saudi and US academia.</p>

